<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="181" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva, 2017" authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2017" box="[199,330,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Disteniidae" genus="Kozlovellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,330,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Kozlovellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[482,613,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[482,613,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Cosmisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
primarily by the absence of a tuft of setae on antennomeres V or V–VI. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques" box="[311,597,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" refString="Marques, M. I. &amp; Napp, D. S. (2003) Analise cladistica da tribo Rhopalophorini Blanchard, 1845 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (4), 491 - 545." type="journal article" year="2003">Marques &amp; Napp (2003)</bibRefCitation>
(translated): “In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[798,929,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[798,929,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Cosmisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there is the presence of tufts of setae with condensed and uniform appearance, surrounding the entire article, in articles V and/or V–VI, synapomorphic condition”. Zajciw (1962) pointed out that “... although the genus is characteriZed by the presence of tufts of setae on the V or V–VI antennal articles, actually a Very important feature, it also counts with a species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1288,1436,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudicorne">
<emphasis box="[1288,1436,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. nudicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Panama) [= 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1861" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1861" box="[310,623,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martyr">
<emphasis box="[310,426,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. martyr</emphasis>
Thomson, 1861
</taxonomicName>
, synonymy by 
<bibRefCitation author="Giesbert" box="[813,1135,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" refString="Giesbert, E. F. &amp; Chemsak, J. A. (1993) A revieW of the Rhopalophorini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of North and Central America. Insecta Mundi, 7 (1 - 2), 27 - 64." type="journal article" year="1993">Giesbert &amp; Chemsak 1993</bibRefCitation>
], and a Variety, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gounelle" authorityName="Gounelle" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneum">
<emphasis box="[1336,1436,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">cyaneum</emphasis>
Gounelle
</taxonomicName>
[apparently they are talking about 
<taxonomicName authority="Monne &amp; Magno, 1988" authorityName="Monne &amp; Magno" authorityYear="1988" box="[662,1216,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cyaneum" subSpecies="psilocerum">
<emphasis box="[662,931,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. cyaneum psilocerum</emphasis>
Monné &amp; Magno, 1988
</taxonomicName>
, a subspecies from BraZil, Paraíba, which was mentioned by Zajciw (1962) as a form from this BraZilian state], without this feature”. Being that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[273,404,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,404,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Cosmisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the largest genus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2017" box="[658,837,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Rhopalophorini">Rhopalophorini</taxonomicName>
, with 41 species, and this feature being absent only in one, it is accepted Zajciw’s (
<emphasis box="[475,509,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">l.c.</emphasis>
) [
<emphasis box="[535,566,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">sic</emphasis>
] affirmation, and the presence of tufts of setae on the antennae is considered as synapomorphic for the genus. Actually, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bates" box="[783,932,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" refString="Bates, H. W. (1892) Additions to the Longicornia of Mexico and Central America, With remarks on some of the previously recorded species. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1892, 143 - 183." type="journal article" year="1892">Bates (1892)</bibRefCitation>
: “One example, differing in nothing from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martyra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. martyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis box="[260,291,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">sic</emphasis>
] except in the absence of hair-brush from the antennae… It is possible it may be only a Variety or aberration.” Apparently the same Variation occurs in 
<taxonomicName authority="Gounelle, 1911" authorityName="Gounelle" authorityYear="1911" box="[778,1106,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneum">
<emphasis box="[778,915,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. cyaneum</emphasis>
Gounelle, 1911
</taxonomicName>
. If so, it is possible that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudicorne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. nudicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1861" box="[476,585,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martyr">
<emphasis box="[476,585,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. martyr</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or that both (
<taxonomicName box="[747,894,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudicorne">
<emphasis box="[747,894,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. nudicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[949,1106,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psilocerum">
<emphasis box="[949,1106,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. psilocerum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are different species. In this case, comparing 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva, 2017" authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2017" box="[340,471,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Disteniidae" genus="Kozlovellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[340,471,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Kozlovellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1834" box="[748,879,656,679]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[748,879,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Cosmisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirby, 1818" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1818" box="[892,1285,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Saperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scopulicornis">
<emphasis box="[892,1142,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">Saperda scopulicornis</emphasis>
Kirby, 1818
</taxonomicName>
, it is possible to see that antennomere IV is longer than III, while in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[760,938,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scopulicorne">
<emphasis box="[760,938,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. scopulicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is distinctly shorter than III, and the distal antennomeres are not notably shorter than III (distinctly shorter in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[897,1075,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cosmisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scopulicorne">
<emphasis box="[897,1075,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="181">C. scopulicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
